ARRAYS:
- To store similar items or group of items
- Whenever you have group of similar items and you wish to store them, we should prefer Arrays
Syntax:
   1. dataType[] arrayName = {value1, value2, value3.................valueN};

   2. dataType[] arrayName = new dataType[countOfItemsYouWantToStore];

- Arrays and loops go together. To store multiple values, we prefer arrays and to perform operations over multiple values we use loops
- Just to print values in an array: System.out.println(Arrays.toString(NameOfArray));

-Limitation:
 Arrays can hold only fix values
 Arrays are not dynamic enough

 ---> Collections